{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking tray (20 x 30 cm), oven","id":"r256215","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/--SxK1uoPNdw\/XZQunh2t58I\/AAAAAAAAcVQ\/FrcvwBNm4dAXK3IS5HNSlxTExBWLgr1wQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_3RG969HPyPXkNu5m.png","title":"Flaky salmon pie with herb dressing","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Salmon filling"},{"content":"1 eschalot"},{"content":"1 fresh long red chilli, trimmed"},{"content":"1 tbsp pickled capers, drained"},{"content":"200 g Greek-style natural yoghurt"},{"content":"2 pinches ground black pepper"},{"content":"2 eggs"},{"content":"300 - 400 g hot smoked salmon, flaked into bite-size pieces"},{"content":"olive oil spray (see Tip)"},{"content":"8 sheets filo pastry"},{"content":"3 tbsp panko breadcrumbs"},{"content":"2 tsp sesame seeds"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Herb dressing"},{"content":"5 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only"},{"content":"5 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only"},{"content":"1 garlic clove"},{"content":"2 pinches salt"},{"content":"60 g extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"20 g lemon juice"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"24.7 g","fat":"28.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"19 g","calories":"1837.7 kJ \/ 437.6 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Salmon filling"},{"content":"Place eschalot and chilli into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add capers, yoghurt, pepper and eggs and mix <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add salmon and gently stir to combine."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 190°C. Spray a baking tray (20 x 30 cm) with oil."},{"content":"Spray 1 sheet of filo pastry with oil. Line prepared baking tray with oiled pastry, allowing pastry to overlap edges. Spray a second sheet of filo pastry with oil and layer on top of previous sheet. Repeat spraying and layering with 2 more sheets of the pastry. Sprinkle pastry with breadcrumbs and spread with reserved salmon mixture. Fold in any overlapping edges. Spray all remaining 4 sheets of pastry with oil and layer over salmon filling. Tuck in any overlapping edges and score pie with a diamond pattern. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and bake for 18-20 minutes (190°C) until golden and crisp. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Herb dressing"},{"content":"Place parsley, basil, garlic and salt into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add oil and lemon juice and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Drizzle salmon pie with dressing and serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can use melted butter, instead of olive oil spray, when layering pastry sheets."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","6 portions"]}